The paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum semipaired dominating set in graphs, which is a problem related to domination and covering in graphs. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The paper also presents algorithms for specific graph classes such as interval graphs, trees, bipartite graphs, and split graphs, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Combinatorics (cs.CC) categories.
